    "slug": "5-digital-payment-systems-that-could-transform-online-fundraising",
    "link": "https://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/12/22/5-digital-payment-systems-that-could-transform-online-fundraising/",
    "title": {
      "rendered": "5 Digital Payment Systems That Could Transform Online Fundraising"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-20679\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/5-Digital-Payment-Systems-Online-Fundraising-Fcebook.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>In the late 1990&#8217;s nonprofits began to launch websites, experiment with email marketing, and sign up for their first &#8220;Donate Now&#8221; service. Then, in the late 2000&#8217;s nonprofits embraced social networking sites, first Myspace and YouTube, then Facebook and Twitter. Now, in the late 2010&#8217;s, we&#8217;re on the verge of yet another seismic shift that will have a profound impact upon online communications and fundraising \u2013 the rise of digital payment systems.</p>\n<p>In short, digital payment systems (in some cases referred to as mobile wallets or social payments) allow donors to make a debit or credit card donation in only\u00a02-3 clicks/taps. Most services only allow email opt-in which means your nonprofit must craft an email-focused donor cultivation process unique to digital payments donors. If the donation is made via Facebook, Twitter, or YouTube, you&#8217;ll also have the opportunity to cultivate donors directly via Facebook, Twitter, and YouTube.</p>\n<p>Digital payment systems are in their early days and there are hundreds of others in use that are not listed below. Over the next decade the fittest will survive and those that cannot compete will be weeded out. However, the five listed below are systems you should prioritize at this early stage. Study each one, sign up for their services if you can, and then we&#8217;ll all learn together over the next 2-3 years how to effectively use these tools. It&#8217;s likely just a matter of time until donors will land on your nonprofit&#8217;s &#8220;Donate&#8221; page and be given the option to donate instantly with a digital payment\u00a0login. In fact, Apple Pay is already available to those nonprofits that use <a href=\"https://www.blackbaud.com/apple-pay\"><strong>Blackbaud&#8217;s Merchant Services</strong></a>.</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">1. Facebook Fundraising Tools</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Currently only available to nonprofits in the United States. Facebook digital payments for nonprofits could eventually be extended to <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/help/863171203733904/\">Facebook Messenger Payments</a> and Instagram (owned by Facebook).<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/07/10/what-your-nonprofit-needs-to-know-about-facebooks-new-fundraising-tools/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-20649 aligncenter\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/learnmore.jpg?resize=115%2C40\" alt=\"\" width=\"115\" height=\"40\" /></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/07/10/what-your-nonprofit-needs-to-know-about-facebooks-new-fundraising-tools/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20651\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HSUS.png?resize=600%2C360\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"360\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HSUS.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/HSUS.png?resize=300%2C180&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Twitter Donations</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Currently only available to select nonprofits in the United States.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/12/04/how-twitter-donations-work-what-your-nonprofit-needs-to-know/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20649\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/learnmore.jpg?resize=115%2C40\" alt=\"\" width=\"115\" height=\"40\" /></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/12/04/how-twitter-donations-work-what-your-nonprofit-needs-to-know/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20653\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-11-1.png?resize=600%2C390\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-11-1.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-11-1.png?resize=300%2C195&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Apple Pay</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Currently only available to select nonprofits in the United States.<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.apple.com/newsroom/2016/11/a-touch-of-giving-with-apple-pay.html\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20649\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/learnmore.jpg?resize=115%2C40\" alt=\"\" width=\"115\" height=\"40\" /></a></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.apple.com/newsroom/2016/11/a-touch-of-giving-with-apple-pay.html\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20657\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/applepay-unicef-1.jpg?resize=600%2C400\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/applepay-unicef-1.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/applepay-unicef-1.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><br />\n</strong></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">4. PayPal\u00a0Express Checkout</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Available to all nonprofits that use PayPal. Donors must activate <a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/us/webapps/mpp/one-touch-checkout\">PayPal One Touch</a> to use.</strong><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/us/webapps/mpp/express-checkout\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-20649 size-full\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/learnmore.jpg?resize=115%2C40\" width=\"115\" height=\"40\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.paypal.com/us/webapps/mpp/express-checkout\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20669\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Donation-Summary.jpg?resize=600%2C400\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Donation-Summary.jpg?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Donation-Summary.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: center;\">5. Android Pay</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><a href=\"https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/6327868\">YouTube Donation Cards</a> are currently available to nonprofits participating in <a href=\"https://www.google.com/nonprofits/\">Google&#8217;s Nonprofit Program</a> in the United States and the United Kingdom. Android Pay digital payments could eventually extend to other <a href=\"https://www.google.com/intl/en_US/about/products/\">Google Products</a>.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.android.com/pay/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20649\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/learnmore.jpg?resize=115%2C40\" alt=\"\" width=\"115\" height=\"40\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.android.com/pay/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20670\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/YouTube-Donation-Cards.png?resize=600%2C435\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"435\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/YouTube-Donation-Cards.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/YouTube-Donation-Cards.png?resize=300%2C218&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /><br />\n</a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
